#   GIT-002: object-by-object OFS-only writer â€” one growing log per shard, never REF_DELTA

##  Input

### Context

Child of [GIT-001]. The store's two write paths diverge: local commits go through `KEEPPackFeed` (`keeper/KEEP.c:1652`) which emits OFS_DELTA only when the base is raw in the same pack (`keep_find_raw_in_pack`) and falls back to REF_DELTA otherwise (`:1724`); ingest (`KEEPIngestFile:2238`) `u8bFeed`s a whole foreign pack verbatim. Converge both onto ONE per-object append â€” a dog/git format function that writes raw objects + OFS_DELTA exclusively, base anywhere earlier in the log, addressed purely by offset â€” so keeper's `KEEPPackFeed`, the GIT-003 ingest funnel, AND the js/JABC binding all call one writer (the binding holds no pack-log logic). This is the foundational change; everything else in [GIT-001] builds on it. See [PackLog], [CLAUDE].

 -  Dual writers: `KEEPPackFeed` (Feed-time delta decision) and the ingest verbatim append are separate code with separate delta policy; a format change must be written twice and they can drift.
 -  REF_DELTA on write: `dtype = in_pack ? PACK_OBJ_OFS_DELTA : PACK_OBJ_REF_DELTA` (`KEEP.c:1724`) is the single line that injects sha-addressed deltas into storage â€” the source of the cross-file recursion and droppability hazards [GIT-001] removes.
 -  OFS candidate is pack-batch-scoped: `keep_find_raw_in_pack` only scans the in-progress pack's entries, so cross-batch near-identical objects re-store raw; one growing log lets OFS reference any earlier object in the shard.

### Goals
 -  One per-object append writer in dog/git that emits raw objects + OFS_DELTA exclusively (never REF_DELTA), base any earlier object in the open shard log, addressed purely by offset.
 -  Converge keeper's `KEEPPackFeed`, the GIT-003 ingest funnel, and the GIT-007 JABC binding onto that single append code path (the binding holds no pack-log logic).

### Constraints
 -  OFS varint is the only thing rewritten â€” keep the deflated delta-instruction bytes; recompute the header offset as `cur_pos - base_pos`. No re-deltification, no re-deflate on the verbatim-base path. Use `dog/git/PACK.h` `PACKu8sFeedObjHdr` + the OFS varint encoder; no open-coded headers ([CLAUDE] Â§10, no ptr arithmetic).
 -  Preserve the intra-pack type order invariant ([PackLog] Â§"Intra-pack object order"): non-decreasing commitâ†’treeâ†’blobâ†’tag for canonical writes; `strict_order` stays for Feed, ingest emits in dependency order (GIT-003).
 -  Layering: the byte-level append + the OFS varint encoder live in dog/git (beside `PACKu8sFeedObjHdr`), taking a caller-provided log buffer + resolved base bytes/offset â€” no refs, index, or singleton. keeper keeps the policy (`KEEPObjSha`, base resolution via `keep_find_raw_in_pack`/`KEEPGet`, `WHIFFHashlet60`, indexing, the FILEBook growable log); reuse `DELTEncode`/`ZINFDeflate`, no fresh re-rolls.
 -  Delete the duplicated OFS encoder: `keeper/KEEP.c:1544 pack_feed_ofs` and `js/pack.hpp:23 JABCPackFeedOfs` are two hand-rolled copies â€” replace both with one `PACKu8sFeedOfs` in dog/git (the missing encode counterpart to `PACKDrainOfs`).
 -  Base must precede dependent (forward-reference free) â€” the writer only ever deltas against an already-appended object.

